<li>Cricket Wireless</li>
<li>MetroPCS</li>
<li>Boost Mobile</li>
<li>Virgin Mobile</li>
</ul>

<h2>11. Privacy and Security</h2>
<p>We take the privacy and security of your SMS communications seriously:</p>
<ul>
<li>We do not share your phone number with third parties for marketing purposes</li>
<li>SMS messages are sent via Twilio, a trusted and secure messaging platform</li>
<li>Links in SMS messages are short URLs (e.g., neoatyourservice.com/r/abc123) that redirect to secure HTTPS recording pages</li>
<li>We track SMS delivery status for troubleshooting purposes only</li>
</ul>
<p>For more information about how we handle your data, please see our <a href="/privacy-policy" style="color: #2563eb;">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

<h2>12. Spam and Abuse Prevention</h2>
<p>We do not send spam messages. All SMS notifications from Neo are transactional and directly related to your service usage. If you believe you have received a fraudulent message claiming to be from Neo:</p>
<ul>
<li>Do not click any links</li>
<li>Forward the message to support@neoatyourservice.com</li>
<li>Report the sender to your mobile carrier</li>
</ul>

<h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this SMS Messaging Policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by email or through the Neo service. Your continued use of SMS notifications after such changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

<h2>14. Compliance</h2>
<p>Our SMS messaging practices comply with:</p>
<ul>
<li>Telephone Consumer Protection Act (TCPA)</li>
<li>CAN-SPAM Act</li>
<li>CTIA Messaging Principles and Best Practices</li>
<li>Mobile Marketing Association (MMA) Consumer Best Practices</li>
<li>Twilio's Acceptable Use Policy</li>
</ul>

